The paper deals with the analysis of consistency between two types of diagrams used in software engineering, namely object diagrams and class diagrams. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the formalization of the variability in the semantics of these diagrams, which involves the use of feature models and parametrized analysis. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL), logic in computer science (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and databases (cs.DB), as these areas often deal with formal models and analysis techniques.
